notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-27T18:11:19.290Z",codex-agent,"author=codex-agent,created_at=now,text=Scaffold entrypoint uses CommonJS module.exports for zero-config runtime compatibility without requiring package type/module wiring."
  "2026-04-27T18:11:38.228Z",codex-agent,Scaffold entrypoint uses CommonJS module.exports for zero-config runtime compatibility without requiring package type/module wiring.
learnings[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-27T18:11:22.254Z",codex-agent,"author=codex-agent,created_at=now,text=For retry-safe CLI scaffolds, treat matching existing files as unchanged and only fail when file contents diverge; this preserves idempotency while preventing silent clobbering."
  "2026-04-27T18:11:41.046Z",codex-agent,"For retry-safe CLI scaffolds, treat matching existing files as unchanged and only fail when file contents diverge to preserve idempotency without silent clobbering."
